Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
create_module_model(25.10)                          create_module_model(25.10)

Name
       create_module_model - Creates a module model

Syntax
       create_module_model

       [-help]

       [-allow_port_mismatch]

       [-cell<string>]

       [-phys_hier]

       [-tag <tag_name>]

       [-type  {1801 boundary_model etm extraction_context flexIlm ilm latency
       lef mmmc pin_assign pnr pnr_shell scan_info spef timing_context gds}]

       Creates a module model. It honors  the  set_module_model  -default_cre-
       ate_options command settings.

Parameters
       -allow_port_mismatch
              Creates a new updated LEF. It provides an ability to bring in an
              updated model with mis-matched ports to top-level design.

              Note:  This parameter can be specified with the lef type (-type)
              of module models.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -cell< string>
              Specifies the cell to save. By default, current top cell will be
              saved.

              Note: For 2D designs, the -cell parameter should be used for pnr
              type of module model only.

              Note: For 3D IC designs, the -cell  parameter  can  be  used  to
              specify  a  list  of  partition names or design name to save for
              pnr, lef, or pre_pnr types of module models.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for  each  create_module_model parameter. For a de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:

              man create_module_model

       -phys_hier
              Creates the whole physical hierarchy.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -tag <tag_name>
              Specifies tag name of the saved model.

              Note: You cannot use `latest' as a tag name as it is a  reserved
              keyword for the latest tag.

              * If  a  model is created from an Innovus session that is opened
                by the update_module_model command, then the same tag name  of
                the  current  loaded design will be used if this option is not
                specified.

              * This option is required  if  a  block-level  design  has  been
                opened  explicitly.  You only  need to specify this tag option
                for one model type. For subsequently created model types,  the
                same tag can be used if it has not been specified.

              * If  the  tag  information  is  not  available, the create_mod-
                ule_model command displays an error message.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -type {1801 boundary_model etm extraction_context flexIlm ilm latency
       lef mmmc pin_assign pnr pnr_shell scan_info spef timing_context gds}
              Specifies the type(s) of module model. The following is the list
              of the supported model types:

              * 1801: UPF for power domain

              * boundary_model: Boundary model for timing analysis

              * etm: Extraction timing model

              * extraction_context: Extraction context model

              * flexilm: Flexible interface logic model

              * gds: Graphical design system model

              * ilm: Interface logic model

              * latency: Clock latency information

              * lef: LEF abstract

              * mmmc: Multi-mode multi-corner definition

              * pin_assign:  Pin file from savePtnPin

              * pnr: Innovus DB

              * pnr_shell: Reduced pnr model where only  the  first  level  of
                logics is kept.

              * scan_info: Scan chain information

              * spef: SPEF file from RC extraction

              * timing_context: Timing context model

              Note:  Use  the  -type  1801  to save UPF associated with an ILM
              model so that you do not have to keep a track where is the  cor-
              responding UPF of an ilm.

              Note:  You  can specify a list of model types to create multiple
              types of module models at a time.

              Note: The pnr_shell model type is similar to the  flexilm  model
              but it only has first level of logics.

              Note:  The  create_module_model  -type  spef honors the set_mod-
              ule_model -active_rc_corners command to output SPEF(s)  for  the
              specified  RC  corners. By default, multi corner SPEFs are saved
              as    gzip.    The    output    SPEF(s)     are     saved     at
              <iHDB_root>/<cell>/<tag>/spef/<topCell>.<cornerName>.spef.gz

              Note:  If  the  -rc_corner parameter of the rcOut command is not
              specified,   the   name   of   the   SPEF   output    file    is
              <iHDB_root>/<cell>/<tag>/spef/<topCell>.spef.gz

              Note:  You  can use the timing_context or extraction_context add
              on types for creating a timing or extraction context model,  re-
              spectively, for a specific cell or a master/clone instance. This
              context  model  can be loaded additionally with the design later
              in the flow.

              Default: pnr and lef

              Data_type: enum, optional

Example
              * The following command creates ilm type of  module  model  that
                has the postRoute tag.

                create_module_model -type ilm -tag postRoute

